latestIgtvVideos.title: Bacon & Egg Bake | Buttermilk Biscuits
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Shake up your morning routine with our bacon and egg bake! 🥓🍳 We used avocado and spicy mayo to kick up our breakfast sandwich, get creative and use whatever you like! 🙌

1. Preheat your oven to 400°.
2. Line muffin tin with strips of your favorite bacon.
3. Crack eggs into the wells and bake until set, 15-18 minutes.
4. Top biscuits with your eggs and bacon and anything else you like!

latestIgtvVideos.title: Sweet Potato Whoopie Pies | Sweet Potato Biscuits
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
If you need one last sweet recipe from us for 2019, try this one! 
1.  Allow Sweet Potato Biscuits to theaw in the fridge overnight.

2. Preheat oven to 350°. 3. Cut thawed biscuits in half.

4. Mix 1/2 cup sugar with 2 tablespoons cinnamon in a mixing bowl.

5. Roll biscuits into balls and roll in sugar mixture.

6. Bake until golden brown and allow to cool for at least 45 minutes.

7. Fill with marshmallow fluff or frosting of your choice and enjoy!

latestIgtvVideos.title: Goat Cheese & Mushroom Dip | Buttermilk Biscuits
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Treat your holiday guests to a wreath they'll love to eat! 🎄

1. Allow biscuits to thaw in the refrigerator overnight.

2. Preheat oven to 350°. Flour a flat surface and cut biscuits into fourths.

3. Roll into long pieces and braid together into a wreath around a baking sheet (we used a pizza sheet!). Brush with melted butter and sprinkle with thyme.

4. Bake until golden brown, 15 minutes or so, keep an eye on it!

5. While the biscuits are baking mix ¾ of a container of ricotta with a small log of goat cheese and spread into baking dish.

6. Sautee baby bella or any kind of mushrooms you like with butter, thyme, and garlic.

7. Place mushrooms on top of goat cheese mixture, sprinkle parmesan cheese on top, and bake for 15-20 minutes.

8. Put oven on broil and watch for the cheese to bubble.

9. Remove from oven and allow to cool a few minutes before you place the dip in the middle of the wreath and the guests dig in!
